    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files to create/modify:**\n\n### 1. NEW — `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`\nCore implementation (mirrors `user-agent.ts` pattern):\n- `Geo` interface with 7 optional string fields\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map for 10 country codes\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — extracts Vercel `x-vercel-ip-*` headers, with `cf-ipcountry` as fallback for `countryCode`\n- `geo({ headers }): Geo` — wrapper matching the `userAgent({ headers })` signature\n- `isInRegion(geo, regions): boolean` — case-insensitive `countryCode` check\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2): number` — Haversine formula, returns km\n- No external imports needed (pure TS, no library dependency unlike `user-agent.ts`)\n\n### 2. NEW — `packages/next/geo.js`\nCommonJS entry point, mirrors `server.js` exactly: creates a `geoExports` object, sets `module.exports = geoExports`, then sets each `exports.xxx` individually for named ESM imports.\n\n### 3. NEW — `packages/next/geo.d.ts`\nType definition entry, mirrors `server.d.ts`: re-exports all symbols from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo` using `export`/`export type`.\n\n### 4. MODIFY — `packages/next/package.json`\nInsert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` into the `\"files\"` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical: **g** follows **f**).\n\n### 5. NEW — `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`\n9 tests using Node.js built-in `node:test` + `node:assert`:\n- All Vercel header fields extracted correctly\n- `cf-ipcountry` fallback works\n- Vercel header takes precedence over Cloudflare\n- Missing headers → all `undefined`\n- Country name lookup\n- `isInRegion` matching/non-matching/undefined\n- NY→London distance ≈ 5570 km (±50 km tolerance)",
